    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1819-08-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1819-08-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="103" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d103">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Glenn</persName>,
                                    district attorney, to Mr. <persName type="to">McCulloch</persName>, collector.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Baltimore</hi>
                    </placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1819-08-24">
                        <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 24, 1819</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The inclosed letter was this day
                                handed to me by Mr. Purviance, with a request that it might be
                                transmitted to you.</p>
                <p>I will thank you to take steps such as your official duty require to
                                frustrate the illegal purpose which Daniels appears to have in view,
                                and to let me hear from you as early as convenient on the
                                subject.</p>
                <p>Be pleased to return me the letter inclosed.</p>
                <p>Yours, respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ELIAS GLENN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
